Package: LibeRation
Type: Package
Title: Population Pharmacometric Simulation and Estimation
Version: 0.9.1
Authors@R: person("Sven C.", "van Dijkman",
    email = "svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Sven C. van Dijkman [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Sven C. van Dijkman <svdijkman@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: NONMEM-compatible population PK/PD model specification,
    simulation, estimation, diagnostics, and graphical workflow management
    with one C++ numerical runtime. Implements ADVAN1-4, ADVAN6, ADVAN11-13,
    arbitrary linear matrix propagation, analytical and nonlinear periodic
    steady state, exact automatic differentiation, thirteen population
    estimation methods, declarative continuous, categorical, count,
    event-time, competing-risk, arbitrary-state continuous-time and
    observed/hidden Markov and semi-Markov likelihoods, correlated joint
    endpoints, generalized nested/crossed random effects, ARMA residual
    processes, nonlinear EKF/UKF and particle state-space inference, and
    continuous-discrete stochastic differential equations. Also provides
    filtering, retrospective smoothing, stochastic simulation, diagnostics,
    advanced editable ODE templates, and versioned projects. Models use the established
    LibeRation R syntax or the restricted C++ expression form.
